Parliament, Tuesday, 13 November 2018 – The Joint Constitutional Review Committee will tomorrow, 14 November 2018, continue with its deliberations on the draft report on a possible review of section 25 of the Constitution. Details are as follows: 
	Date: Wednesday, 14 November 2018
	Time: 14:00
	Venue: Committee Room, Old Assembly Chamber, Ground Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CO-CHAIRPERSON OF THE JOINT CONSTITUTIONAL REVIEW COMMITTEE, MR LEWIS NZIMANDE AND ACTING CO-CHAIRPERSON, MR STAN MAILA. For media enquiries or interviews, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Rajaa Azzakani (Ms)
	Tel: 021 403 8437
	Cell: 081 703 9542
	E-mail: razzakani@parliament.gov.za It takes 14 months to prepare the annual Budget for its introduction in the National Assembly.Read more